1:01:15.367 --> 1:01:17.151
What does that matter?

1:01:17.325 --> 1:01:19.806
I will not be complicit
in the illicit use
of ill-gotten booty.

1:01:19.980 --> 1:01:24.158
Uh... Fine. We'’ll divide it
amongst the townspeople.

1:01:24.332 --> 1:01:26.421
Swear to it.What?

1:01:26.595 --> 1:01:28.380
Place your hand
on this Harper'’s Seal

1:01:28.554 --> 1:01:31.688
and swear that you will indeed
distribute all the wealth
you take

1:01:31.862 --> 1:01:33.777
amongst the people
of Neverwinter.

1:01:33.951 --> 1:01:36.388
Sure, fine.

1:01:40.087 --> 1:01:41.610
Go on, Ed.

1:01:41.785 --> 1:01:44.309
Promise you'’ll give
Forge'’s money to the people.

1:01:49.967 --> 1:01:51.751
Promise I'’ll...

1:01:51.925 --> 1:01:54.449
give Forge'’s money
to the people of Neverwinter.

1:01:54.623 --> 1:01:56.147
Keep this.

1:01:57.322 --> 1:02:00.804
You may not yet
believe your words, but I do.

1:02:02.240 --> 1:02:05.286
Yeah. Good for you.
Simon, hold onto this.

1:02:05.460 --> 1:02:06.940
Now, where'’s the helmet?

1:02:07.114 --> 1:02:09.638
In the bowels of the Underdark.The Underdark?

1:02:09.813 --> 1:02:11.728
Weren'’t you trying
to keep it safe?
Why would you put it down there?

1:02:11.902 --> 1:02:14.600
Because it is the last place
that anyone
who values their life would go.

1:02:14.774 --> 1:02:16.254
Sounds lovely.Quite the opposite.

1:02:16.428 --> 1:02:18.952
I-I know. I was being ironic.

1:02:19.126 --> 1:02:22.826
I find irony is a blade
that cuts he who wields it
most especially.

1:02:23.000 --> 1:02:25.872
Yeah?
Is that what you find, Xenk?

1:02:26.046 --> 1:02:28.005
There is an entrance east
of the Sword Mountains

1:02:28.179 --> 1:02:29.615
in the Kryptgarden Forest,

1:02:29.789 --> 1:02:32.792
from which we may descend
to the ruins of Dolblunde.

1:02:34.359 --> 1:02:37.884
If I may be so bold,
what caused you
to renounce the Harpers?

1:02:40.713 --> 1:02:42.976
Being a Harper
got my wife killed.

1:02:43.150 --> 1:02:45.283
I'’m sorry.

1:02:45.457 --> 1:02:47.198
Did her assailants find justice?

1:02:47.372 --> 1:02:48.982
The Thayans, you mean?

1:02:50.418 --> 1:02:51.550
No.

1:02:51.724 --> 1:02:53.726
The Thayans
are not all malevolent.

1:02:55.162 --> 1:02:57.730
I was a boy when Szass Tam
seized control of Thay.

1:03:00.951 --> 1:03:02.996
I saw firsthand
the horrors of the spell.

1:03:04.345 --> 1:03:07.087
Honorable men
turned to monsters.

1:03:07.261 --> 1:03:10.221
Minds wiped clean in moments.

1:03:10.395 --> 1:03:13.964
Parents
turning on their own child.

1:03:34.245 --> 1:03:36.813
I escaped, alive,

1:03:38.031 --> 1:03:40.207
but forever changed.

1:03:40.381 --> 1:03:43.994
You and I have both lost
a part of ourselves.

1:03:44.168 --> 1:03:46.910
All that matters
is what we do
with what remains.

1:03:47.736 --> 1:03:49.434
I told you
what I'’m gonna do.

1:03:49.608 --> 1:03:51.479
I'’m gonna break into
Castle Never
and get my family back.

1:03:52.263 --> 1:03:53.481
And the tablet?

1:03:53.655 --> 1:03:55.832
You plan to resurrect
your wife.Yeah.

1:03:56.833 --> 1:03:59.096
Very well.

1:03:59.270 --> 1:04:02.012
I'’d only ask that
you consider that this plane we
call "life" is but one of many.

1:04:02.186 --> 1:04:03.404
Uh-huh.

1:04:03.578 --> 1:04:05.537
To drag your lady-love
back to her old life

1:04:05.711 --> 1:04:07.321
is to deprive her
of her new one.

1:04:07.495 --> 1:04:10.150
Can someone else
ride next to this guy?

1:04:19.856 --> 1:04:21.509
Follow me to the orifice.

1:04:24.817 --> 1:04:26.427
The orifice?

1:04:28.038 --> 1:04:30.562
The Underdark
has many entrances.

1:04:33.304 --> 1:04:35.567
This is one of
the less conspicuous.

1:04:43.357 --> 1:04:44.706
I'’ll go last.

1:04:46.534 --> 1:04:49.886
It'’s a day'’s trek.
I'’ve chosen a path
to avoid the populace.

1:04:50.060 --> 1:04:52.453
Stay close
and quiet.

1:04:52.627 --> 1:04:56.675
Whatever you'’ve heard
of this place is merely
a fraction of its true danger.

1:04:58.242 --> 1:05:00.244
Should the way
become too dim,

1:05:00.418 --> 1:05:03.334
you may take my hand,
and I will lead you.

1:05:06.337 --> 1:05:08.992
I'’ll tell you right now,
I'’m not taking his hand.

1:05:20.438 --> 1:05:23.267
Keep your guard up.
I don'’t trust this guy.

1:05:24.137 --> 1:05:26.270
Even though
he'’s helping us?

1:05:26.444 --> 1:05:28.794
Ah, he'’s got something
up his sleeve.

1:05:28.968 --> 1:05:31.188
